reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not a sitting stool
reviews.reviewText: This was super easy to put together for which I’d very much like to thank the creators that I didn’t have to tear up my hands with tools. The lug nuts needed for the top were already in place and it was intuitive to screw the two legs together to make them longer and the screw to the top and put the soft rubber caps they include on the bottoms and sit it up. It looks perfectly sturdy for whatever you would want to sit on it but I suspect an adult human would be pushing its tolerance. It’s so easy I’m pretty sure given enough time my 6 yr old niece would pretty quickly figure out how to assemble it. I’ve had some real wrestling matches with putting together furniture so I’m extremely thankful for this one’s simplicity. The table/stool is exactly as I envisioned from the ad for the purpose I wanted it for. No main star negatives and only one took for sturdiness as I would worry about it tilting on a child that can’t sit still if they decided to use it as a seat or to reach something since it’s very lightweight and let’s face it very few can sit still and they don’t really understand the concept of gravity. I’m pretty sure some days my 3 year old niece wonders if I can anything other than “careful”

reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. This small table has a great finish on it to prevent easy scratches! The assembly process doesn't need an instruction manual it's so easy. 1 minute and it's already up and running. It still includes an instruction manual just in case.It is able to support 140 lbs without giving out. The legs come with nice rubber caps to prevent it slipping or damaging any hard floors. They also hide the only unsightly thing about the table, the small welded metal balls at the end of the feet!The table disassembles as easily as it's put together making for easy storage while it's away!Be careful as this could be mistaken as a chair.
